Best
Balance
Transfer
Credit
Cards
Of
March
2021
Robin
Saks
Frankel
Forbes
Advisor
Staff
Updated:
Mar
3,
2021,
11:10am
Editorial
Note:
Forbes
may
earn
a
commission
on
sales
made
from
partner
links
on
this
page,
but
that
doesn't
affect
our
editors'
opinions
or
evaluations.
A
balance
transfer
card
can
be
a
powerful
tool
in
your
debt-busting
arsenal.
By
taking
advantage
of
a
0%
APR
offer
on
a
credit
card,
you
can
save
money
by
having
all
of
your
payments
go
towards
knocking
out
the
principal
balance
instead
of
some
being
siphoned
away
to
pay
the
interest
charges
incurred
from
carrying
a
balance.
Although
taking
a
breather
from
high-interest
debt
is
a
smart
money
move,
you
should
also
do
your
due
diligence
to
choose
the
balance
transfer
card
that
will
help
you
save
the
most
money
overall.
Most
balance
transfer
cards
charge
a
balance
transfer
fee,
typically
3%
to
5%
of
the
amount
being
transferred.
Calculate
the
amount
you’re
looking
to
transfer
plus
any
balance
transfer
fees,
along
with
how
many
months
you’ll
need
to
pay
off
the
debt
to
find
the
balance
transfer
card
that
makes
the
most
sense
for
your
particular
circumstances.
Here
are
Forbes
Advisor’s
top
picks
for
balance
transfer
cards.
Read
more
Show
